WEBVTT

00:00:24.208 --> 00:00:26.417
It got brighter!

00:00:26.417 --> 00:00:31.958
"ALfheim, Neutral Territory, Legrue Corridor
January 21, 2025"
Night-vision magic? I guess
Spriggans are good for something.

00:00:31.958 --> 00:00:34.667
Put that way, it kind of hurts.

00:00:35.208 --> 00:00:40.583
But you should learn any magic you can.
You're only good at glamours though.

00:00:40.917 --> 00:00:43.583
--Glamours?
--Projecting illusions.

00:00:43.583 --> 00:00:46.583
It's not that useful
in combat, though.

00:00:46.583 --> 00:00:52.250
Well, lame Spriggan magic might be
the difference between life and death.

00:00:54.083 --> 00:00:57.083
That hurt even more.

00:00:58.625 --> 00:01:04.083
<i>The feelings I've hidden</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:01:04.083 --> 00:01:09.583
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:01:19.792 --> 00:01:30.125
<i>Seeking only a miracle, I wander</i>
<i>through an endless darkness</i>

00:01:30.250 --> 00:01:40.833
<i>If I stay here, I won't</i>
<i>ever see the future again</i>

00:01:40.917 --> 00:01:46.167
<i>Tonight the moon summons me again.</i>
<i>Though I still cannot speak,</i>

00:01:46.167 --> 00:01:49.958
<i>I keep crying out in my heart</i>

00:01:51.083 --> 00:01:56.333
<i>My hidden feelings</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:01:56.500 --> 00:02:01.417
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:02:01.583 --> 00:02:07.167
<i>If I can stay stronger a bit longer,</i>

00:02:07.167 --> 00:02:13.250
<i>I will go beyond</i>
<i>this sky right in front of me</i>

00:02:15.042 --> 00:02:21.583
<i>I will reach out towards</i>
<i>the future ahead of me</i>

00:02:27.042 --> 00:02:31.042
"The Legrue Corridor"

00:02:35.417 --> 00:02:39.958
Don't just memorize words by rote.
Learn what the words of power mean,

00:02:39.958 --> 00:02:44.500
and recall them by associating them
with the magic's effects.

00:02:44.833 --> 00:02:49.792
I never thought I'd have to memorize
something like English words in a game.

00:02:49.792 --> 00:02:54.833
Just so you know, the higher-ranked
spells have around 20 words.

00:02:54.833 --> 00:02:59.292
--I'll stick to being a pure fighter...
--No complaining!

00:03:00.125 --> 00:03:03.500
I got a message.
Sorry. Hold on.

00:03:03.500 --> 00:03:04.667
Sure.

00:03:04.958 --> 00:03:09.042
Recon again?
I'm sure it's nothing, but...

00:03:09.875 --> 00:03:14.625
"It was just like I thought.
Be careful, s"

00:03:14.833 --> 00:03:16.792
What's this? "S"?

00:03:16.792 --> 00:03:19.292
Sa... Shi... Su...

00:03:20.208 --> 00:03:22.458
--What's wrong?
--Well...

00:03:22.958 --> 00:03:26.792
--Daddy, incoming signatures.
--Monsters?

00:03:26.792 --> 00:03:28.750
No, players.

00:03:28.750 --> 00:03:31.042
Lots of them. Twelve.

00:03:31.042 --> 00:03:32.292
Twelve?

00:03:33.792 --> 00:03:37.417
I've got a bad feeling.
Let's hide and let them pass.

00:03:37.417 --> 00:03:38.833
But where?

00:03:39.458 --> 00:03:41.792
Leave that to me.

00:03:43.958 --> 00:03:45.583
H-Hey...

00:03:54.583 --> 00:04:00.750
Talk as softly as you can.
If you're too loud, it'll break the spell.

00:04:00.750 --> 00:04:01.875
Roger.

00:04:01.875 --> 00:04:04.625
They'll be in view soon.

00:04:07.208 --> 00:04:11.875
--What is that?
--They're not visible yet, are they?

00:04:11.875 --> 00:04:16.250
It isn't a player. A bat, maybe?
It's red and small.

00:04:26.750 --> 00:04:28.708
H-Hey, what's wrong?

00:04:28.708 --> 00:04:33.000
That's a high-level tracing searcher!
We have to destroy it!

00:04:42.292 --> 00:04:47.042
--We're going to run, Kirito!
--Can't we just hide again?

00:04:47.042 --> 00:04:52.042
The enemy knows we blew up their tracer.
We won't be able to fool them.

00:04:52.042 --> 00:04:57.625
And that was a fire-element familiar.
Which means the approaching party...

00:04:57.875 --> 00:05:00.292
They're Salamanders?

00:05:03.125 --> 00:05:06.917
But what would a group of
Salamanders be doing here?

00:05:06.917 --> 00:05:08.917
It's a lake...

00:05:14.208 --> 00:05:18.792
--Looks like we'll make it.
--Don't drop your guard and fall in.

00:05:22.542 --> 00:05:23.750
Crap.

00:05:31.083 --> 00:05:34.250
--That won't work.
--Then say so sooner.

00:05:34.250 --> 00:05:37.250
It's your fault for being impatient.

00:05:37.250 --> 00:05:41.375
This is an earth-magic barrier,
so physical attacks can't break it.

00:05:41.375 --> 00:05:44.708
--Can we jump in the lake?
--Nope.

00:05:44.708 --> 00:05:49.000
Supposedly, there are extremely
high-level monsters in the water.

00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:53.875
Fighting without an Undine
backing you up would be suicidal.

00:05:53.875 --> 00:05:56.583
Then fighting's our only option.

00:05:56.583 --> 00:06:00.208
That is our only option,
but it might be a bit risky.

00:06:00.208 --> 00:06:04.000
The fact they can use
such high-level earth magic

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:08.208
means they've teamed up
with mages that powerful.

00:06:08.208 --> 00:06:12.375
Leafa, it's not that I don't
trust your skill with a sword,

00:06:12.833 --> 00:06:16.167
but could you back me up
from here on out?

00:06:16.167 --> 00:06:19.708
I want you behind me,
focusing on healing.

00:06:19.708 --> 00:06:22.417
That way, I can fight
without worries.

00:06:47.125 --> 00:06:49.625
<i>They're countering Kirito perfectly!</i>

00:07:02.792 --> 00:07:04.208
Kirito!

00:07:40.250 --> 00:07:43.875
<i>He'll run out of HP at this rate...</i>

00:07:44.250 --> 00:07:45.875
Enough, Kirito!

00:07:45.875 --> 00:07:51.417
If we lose, it'll just mean a few extra
hours of flying! Let's just give up!

00:07:51.417 --> 00:07:52.958
No way.

00:07:53.583 --> 00:07:57.750
As long as I'm alive, I won't
let any party members die.

00:07:57.750 --> 00:08:00.750
I'll never let that happen!

00:08:17.125 --> 00:08:19.875
Damn, what's he doing?

00:08:20.667 --> 00:08:23.792
--This is your only chance!
--Chance?

00:08:23.792 --> 00:08:29.042
Use all the mana you have left to
somehow block the next magic attack!

00:08:29.458 --> 00:08:32.500
B-But that won't help.

00:09:03.917 --> 00:09:05.625
Daddy, now!

00:09:09.833 --> 00:09:12.333
<i>An illusion-attribute spell...</i>

00:09:12.333 --> 00:09:16.542
<i>But it only makes him</i>
<i>look like a big monster.</i>

00:09:32.708 --> 00:09:35.292
Is that you, Kirito?

00:09:50.500 --> 00:09:54.625
Idiots! Don't break formation!
It just looks scary and has a long reach!

00:09:54.625 --> 00:09:59.625
If we stay in formation as planned,
the damage won't be validated!

00:10:12.292 --> 00:10:14.792
E-Explosion magic!

00:10:42.708 --> 00:10:45.333
Retreat! Retreat!

00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:11.583
Stop!

00:11:13.167 --> 00:11:15.750
Kirito, let that one live!

00:11:20.333 --> 00:11:22.667
That was amazing, right?

00:11:22.667 --> 00:11:24.000
Ow...

00:11:24.458 --> 00:11:28.625
Now, why don't you explain who sent you here?

00:11:29.625 --> 00:11:32.625
--K-Kill me if you want!
--Why, you...

00:11:32.625 --> 00:11:36.125
Man, did I go on a rampage!

00:11:39.333 --> 00:11:41.542
Hey, nice fight.

00:11:42.000 --> 00:11:47.208
That was a good plan. If I'd been alone,
I wouldn't have lasted a minute.

00:11:47.208 --> 00:11:49.000
H-Hey, Kirito!

00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:50.542
Now, now...

00:11:50.542 --> 00:11:53.458
So I have an offer for you.

00:11:53.458 --> 00:11:57.667
These are the items
and Yuld I won in this battle.

00:11:57.667 --> 00:12:02.292
If you answer my questions,
I might just let you have them!

00:12:04.667 --> 00:12:05.875
Really?

00:12:05.875 --> 00:12:07.667
Totally.

00:12:11.083 --> 00:12:12.625
Men.

00:12:12.625 --> 00:12:16.042
They don't know how
to be subtle, do they?

00:12:16.792 --> 00:12:23.042
Earlier this evening, G-Takusu...
The mage squad's leader, I mean...

00:12:23.500 --> 00:12:26.750
He texted that I should
meet him here.

00:12:26.750 --> 00:12:30.792
When I logged in, he said he would be
hunting two players with twelve.

00:12:30.792 --> 00:12:36.917
I thought it was bullying, but he said the targets
defeated Kagemune, so it made sense.

00:12:36.917 --> 00:12:39.083
Who's Kagemune?

00:12:39.083 --> 00:12:43.167
The leader of a lancer squad.
He's famous for hunting Sylphs.

00:12:43.167 --> 00:12:48.458
But he got wiped out in battle yesterday
and fled home. You did that, right?

00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:54.083
So why did this G-Takusu guy
come after us?

00:12:54.083 --> 00:12:58.875
I hear it's an order from higher up...
Something about you hindering the plan.

00:12:58.875 --> 00:13:00.667
What plan?

00:13:00.667 --> 00:13:06.792
They wouldn't tell a bottom feeder like me,
but it seems it's something big.

00:13:06.792 --> 00:13:12.125
When I logged in today, I saw a huge
number of troops heading north.

00:13:12.625 --> 00:13:16.500
North... They plan
to clear the World Tree?

00:13:16.500 --> 00:13:17.625
No way.

00:13:17.625 --> 00:13:21.875
The army would need at least
ancient-weapon-class gear...

00:13:21.875 --> 00:13:25.250
...which is what
we've been saving for.

00:13:25.750 --> 00:13:30.958
That's all I know. You weren't lying
about what you said earlier, were you?

00:13:30.958 --> 00:13:34.333
No, I'd never lie about a trade.

00:13:35.958 --> 00:13:41.500
Hey, that monster that was rampaging before...
That was you, right?

00:13:41.500 --> 00:13:43.417
I think so...

00:13:43.417 --> 00:13:45.083
What do you mean?

00:13:45.083 --> 00:13:50.708
That happens sometimes... I snap
in battle and start forgetting things.

00:13:51.125 --> 00:13:52.500
Scary.

00:13:52.500 --> 00:13:57.917
Though I do mostly remember this last one.
I used the spell Yui suggested...

00:13:58.250 --> 00:13:59.583
Now!

00:13:59.583 --> 00:14:02.583
And then I got huge...

00:14:03.042 --> 00:14:06.792
I lost my sword too,
so I just grabbed people.

00:14:06.792 --> 00:14:09.792
You were chomping on them too.

00:14:09.792 --> 00:14:15.875
Come to think of it, I got to feel like
a monster. It was a fun experience.

00:14:15.875 --> 00:14:18.625
Um, what did they taste like?

00:14:18.625 --> 00:14:22.250
The texture and flavor
of nearly burnt grilled beef.

00:14:22.250 --> 00:14:24.583
Never mind. Don't say it.

00:14:40.292 --> 00:14:42.708
So this is Legrue?

00:14:43.042 --> 00:14:44.333
Ow...

00:14:44.333 --> 00:14:47.625
--That one was your fault.
--Seriously!

00:14:47.625 --> 00:14:52.458
But it was just a witty joke
meant to lighten up a tense vibe.

00:14:52.458 --> 00:14:55.958
Next time you do that,
I'll slice you in half.

00:14:55.958 --> 00:14:57.292
Yes, ma'am...

00:15:03.500 --> 00:15:09.875
By the way, didn't you get a message
before those Salamanders attacked us?

00:15:09.875 --> 00:15:13.042
Yeah, I forgot about that.

00:15:13.042 --> 00:15:16.500
What's with Recon?
Did he fall asleep?

00:15:16.500 --> 00:15:20.167
Why don't you try to reach him
on the other side?

00:15:20.167 --> 00:15:25.167
Okay, I'll log out for a second and
check in with him... Wait for me, Kirito.

00:15:25.167 --> 00:15:28.083
Take care of my body, Yui.

00:15:28.083 --> 00:15:29.208
What?

00:15:29.208 --> 00:15:32.750
Watch your dad so he doesn't
do anything to my body.

00:15:32.750 --> 00:15:34.125
Roger!

00:15:34.125 --> 00:15:35.542
Seriously...

00:15:39.417 --> 00:15:40.333
"Are you sure you want to log out?"

00:15:59.458 --> 00:16:00.625
"Shinichi Nagata Missed Call"

00:16:00.625 --> 00:16:01.250
"Shinichi Nagata"

00:16:03.458 --> 00:16:06.917
Hello? Nagata? What's going on?

00:16:06.917 --> 00:16:11.292
<i>You finally picked up!</i>
<i>You're late, Suguha!</i>

00:16:11.292 --> 00:16:13.625
I had in-game problems.

00:16:13.625 --> 00:16:17.750
<i>B-Big trouble!</i>
<i>Sigurd's coming after us...</i>

00:16:17.750 --> 00:16:22.000
<i>N-Not only that, they sold out</i>
<i>the Sylph leader, Sakuya!</i>

00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:24.208
Sold her out?

00:16:24.208 --> 00:16:27.583
What's that mean?
Start from the beginning.

00:16:27.583 --> 00:16:29.167
<i>There's no time...</i>

00:16:29.167 --> 00:16:34.042
<i>Remember when the Salamanders</i>
<i>attacked us in the Ancient Forest?</i>

00:16:34.042 --> 00:16:37.292
<i>Didn't you sense</i>
<i>something odd, Suguha?</i>

00:16:37.292 --> 00:16:40.292
Odd? Did something happen?

00:16:40.292 --> 00:16:44.542
<i>Sigurd said he'd act as a decoy</i>
<i>and drew three of them away.</i>

00:16:44.542 --> 00:16:48.708
--Now that you mention it...
--It wasn't like him.

00:16:48.708 --> 00:16:52.500
<i>Wouldn't he normally</i>
<i>make someone else do it?</i>

00:16:52.500 --> 00:16:53.958
That's true.

00:16:54.750 --> 00:16:57.750
But what does that mean?

00:16:58.042 --> 00:17:00.875
<i>What I'm getting at is...</i>

00:17:00.875 --> 00:17:06.083
<i>He's been colluding with the Salamanders.</i>
<i>Probably for quite a while!</i>

00:17:07.125 --> 00:17:09.708
Do you have any proof?

00:17:09.708 --> 00:17:12.458
<i>Something was bugging me,</i>

00:17:12.458 --> 00:17:17.708
<i>so I've been following Sigurd since</i>
<i>this morning using an invisibility spell.</i>

00:17:17.708 --> 00:17:23.000
And I saw them also putting on
invisibility cloaks in a back alley.

00:17:23.000 --> 00:17:26.208
So I was sure something
was about to happen.

00:17:26.917 --> 00:17:32.500
Deep down in the sewers, there were
two weird guys waiting for them...

00:17:33.125 --> 00:17:36.542
And wouldn't you know it,
they were Salamanders!

00:17:36.542 --> 00:17:42.708
My hunch was right, so as I listened in,
they said they put a tracer on you.

00:17:53.083 --> 00:17:55.292
What happened to you?

00:17:55.292 --> 00:18:00.542
I'm still in the sewers, paralyzed by
a poison arrow. They have me.

00:18:01.667 --> 00:18:04.792
That's why you called me IRL...

00:18:05.333 --> 00:18:07.333
<i>It's not just collusion!</i>

00:18:07.333 --> 00:18:11.542
<i>Sakuya's supposed to form an alliance</i>
<i>with the Cait Siths today.</i>

00:18:11.542 --> 00:18:15.375
<i>So she's secretly heading</i>
<i>to neutral territory.</i>

00:18:15.542 --> 00:18:21.375
<i>Sigurd's going to have a large Salamander</i>
<i>force attack the signing ceremony!</i>

00:18:26.292 --> 00:18:28.167
I have to go!

00:18:28.167 --> 00:18:31.042
--Welcome back, Leafa.
--Welcome back.

00:18:31.042 --> 00:18:33.375
Kirito, I'm sorry.

00:18:34.250 --> 00:18:38.125
I have to take care of
something right away.

00:18:38.125 --> 00:18:41.542
It seems I don't
have time to explain.

00:18:41.542 --> 00:18:45.917
And I probably might not
be able to return here...

00:18:45.917 --> 00:18:48.917
Then you can explain
on the way.

00:18:49.375 --> 00:18:53.250
We have to walk out
of here anyway, right?

00:18:54.417 --> 00:18:55.958
All right.

00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:10.417
In 40 minutes, past Butterfly Valley, the Sylph
and Cait Sith leaders will start a conference.

00:19:10.417 --> 00:19:14.083
--I see. Can I ask some questions?
--Go ahead.

00:19:14.083 --> 00:19:19.792
How do the Salamanders benefit from
attacking the Sylph and Cait Sith leaders?

00:19:19.792 --> 00:19:22.458
First of all, they can interfere
with the alliance forming.

00:19:22.458 --> 00:19:27.500
The Cait Sith wouldn't tolerate their leader
being killed because of a leak from the Sylph.

00:19:27.792 --> 00:19:29.000
Yeah.

00:19:29.458 --> 00:19:33.708
War could break out between
the Cait Siths and Sylphs.

00:19:33.708 --> 00:19:38.958
And if you take out a territory's leader,
you get 30 percent of its money,

00:19:38.958 --> 00:19:42.958
can occupy its towns for 10 days,
and freely levy taxes.

00:19:42.958 --> 00:19:45.208
You can do that?

00:19:45.583 --> 00:19:47.417
So, Kirito...

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:53.833
This is a Sylph problem, so there's
no reason for you to come with me.

00:19:54.417 --> 00:19:57.958
If we go, we probably
won't make it back alive.

00:19:57.958 --> 00:20:01.500
And we'd have to start
over from Sylvain again.

00:20:01.500 --> 00:20:06.875
No, it's even possible that if you want
to reach the top of the World Tree,

00:20:06.875 --> 00:20:11.083
you might be better off
working with the Salamanders.

00:20:12.375 --> 00:20:18.417
If they pull this off, they'll be perfectly
positioned to try to clear the World Tree.

00:20:18.417 --> 00:20:22.625
As a Spriggan, they might
hire you as a mercenary.

00:20:22.625 --> 00:20:28.000
So even if you kill me here,
I won't have any complaints.

00:20:30.792 --> 00:20:34.542
In the end, it's a game,
so anything goes.

00:20:34.542 --> 00:20:39.167
If you want to kill, you kill.
If you want to steal, you steal.

00:20:40.208 --> 00:20:46.417
I've met more people than I care to
who think that way. In a way, it's true.

00:20:46.792 --> 00:20:49.625
I used to think that way too.

00:20:50.708 --> 00:20:56.792
But it's not true. There are things you have
to protect because it is a virtual world.

00:20:56.792 --> 00:21:00.625
I learned that from
someone important to me.

00:21:00.625 --> 00:21:03.333
If you give in
to your urges here,

00:21:03.333 --> 00:21:07.042
the price is that it changes
your personality in real life.

00:21:07.042 --> 00:21:10.250
The player and
the character are one.

00:21:10.250 --> 00:21:15.333
I like you, Leafa.
I want to be your friend.

00:21:15.875 --> 00:21:21.833
No matter what the reason,
attacking someone for my own benefit

00:21:22.625 --> 00:21:25.500
is something I'd never do.

00:21:27.750 --> 00:21:29.417
Kirito...

00:21:35.625 --> 00:21:36.792
Thank you.

00:21:37.458 --> 00:21:41.167
Sorry, that was arrogant of me.
It's a bad habit...

00:21:41.167 --> 00:21:44.083
No, it made me happy.

00:21:45.000 --> 00:21:47.917
Crap... We're wasting time,
aren't we?

00:21:47.917 --> 00:21:49.792
Yui, we're running.
Lead the way!

00:21:50.542 --> 00:21:51.625
Roger!

00:21:51.750 --> 00:21:54.833
--Give me your hand for a sec.
--U-Uh...

00:21:54.833 --> 00:21:56.333
Let's go!

00:22:02.250 --> 00:22:04.667
U-Uh, m-monsters!

00:22:10.750 --> 00:22:12.708
There's the exit!

00:22:17.917 --> 00:22:25.042
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:22:25.042 --> 00:22:34.750
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:22:46.125 --> 00:22:52.875
<i>These endless feelings were</i>
<i>swallowed up into my daily life</i>

00:22:53.250 --> 00:23:00.083
<i>Swaying as they</i>
<i>change shape yet again</i>

00:23:00.458 --> 00:23:07.375
<i>Is it too late now? I ask</i>
<i>myself but receive no answer</i>

00:23:07.500 --> 00:23:15.042
<i>It's all up to me now,</i>
<i>both the ending and the beginning</i>

00:23:15.208 --> 00:23:22.167
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:23:22.167 --> 00:23:29.333
<i>I'm going to spread my wings</i>
<i>and head towards that gentle light</i>

00:23:29.333 --> 00:23:36.708
<i>Carrying the passion</i>
<i>I've lit in my heart</i>

00:23:36.708 --> 00:23:44.958
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:23:47.083 --> 00:23:53.195
Next Time: "General of the Blazing Flame."
